race.comment: DO SOMETHING (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 34.63 beating Paw Louis. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from four starts. Great chance to get the job done again. KEY PHILOSOPHY (6) hit the ground running off the tricky draw and gave a sight in front, boxing on well for a minor when third (34.76) at this track in a Special conditions H over 600m. The form out of his last race has been franked. Expected to feature again. MAGIC SNOWDROP (4) finds it hard to break through. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (43.07) at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Leading chance. STAR STAY (2) is worth a look over a shorter trip this time.
